-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|16 July 1797 || style=\"text-align:center\"|25 July 1797 || [[Jean-Jacques Lenoir-Laroche]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|25 July 1797 || style=\"text-align:center\"|13 February 1798 || [[Jean-Marie Sotin de La Coindi\u00e8re]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|13 February 1798 || style=\"text-align:center\"|2 May 1798 || [[Nicolas Dondeau]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2 May 1798 || style=\"text-align:center\"|29 October 1798 || [[Marie Jean Fran\u00e7ois Philibert Lecarlier d'Ardon]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|29 October 1798 || style=\"text-align:center\"|23 June 1799 || [[Jean-Pierre Duval]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|23 June 1799 || style=\"text-align:center\"|20 July 1799 || [[Claude S\u00e9bastien Bourguignon]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|20 July 1799 || style=\"text-align:center\"|10 November 1799 || [[Joseph Fouch\u00e9]]\n|-\n|rowspan=5|Interior || style=\"text-align:center\"|3 November 1795 || style=\"text-align:center\"|16 July 1797 || [[Pierre B\u00e9n\u00e9zech]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|16 July 1797 || style=\"text-align:center\"|14 September 1797 || [[Fran\u00e7ois de Neufch\u00e2teau]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|14 September 1797 || style=\"text-align:center\"|17 June 1798 || [[Fran\u00e7ois S\u00e9bastien Letourneux]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|17 June 1798 || style=\"text-align:center\"|22 June 1799 || [[Fran\u00e7ois de Neufch\u00e2teau]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|22 June 1799 || style=\"text-align:center\"|10 November 1799 || [[Nicolas Marie Quinette]]\n|-\n|rowspan=4|Navy and colonies || style=\"text-align:center\"|3 November 1795 ||style=\"text-align:center\"| 16 July 1797 || [[Laurent Jean Fran\u00e7ois Truguet]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|16 July 1797 || style=\"text-align:center\"|27 April 1798 || [[Georges Ren\u00e9 Le Peley de Pl\u00e9ville]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|27 April 1798 || style=\"text-align:center\"|2 July 1799 || [[\u00c9tienne Eustache Bruix]]\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2 July 1799 || style=\"text-align:center\"|10 November 1799 || [[Marc Antoine Bourdon de Vatry]]\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Directoire style]]\n* [[Paris in the 18th century]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|20em}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* {{cite book|title=From Louis XIV to Napoleon: The Fate of a Great Power|last=Black|first=Jeremy|authorlink=Jeremy Black (historian)|year=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9780203006382|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vF4k-6TH-FsC&printsec=frontcover}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|title=French Revolution, The|encyclopedia=Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|editor=[[Hugh Chisholm|Chisholm, Hugh]]|volume=11|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1911|url=http://www.gutenberg.org/files/37736/37736-h/37736-h.htm#ar3}}; excerpts are included in this article\n* Church, Clive H., ''The Social Basis of the French Central Bureaucracy under the Directory 1795\u20131799'', in ''Past & Present'' No. 36, April 1967, pp.&nbsp;59\u201372 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/649915 in JSTOR].\n* {{cite book|last1=Doyle|first1=William|authorlink=William Doyle (historian)|title=The Oxford History of the French Revolution|edition=2|year=1990|publisher=Oxford University Press|pages=[https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryoff00doyl/page/318 318\u201340]|isbn=9780199252985|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryoff00doyl/page/318}}\n* {{cite book|last=Fierro|first=Alfred|title=Histoire et dictionnaire de Paris|year=1996|publisher=Robert Laffont|isbn=978-2-221-07862-4}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|first=Fran\u00e7ois|last=Furet |year=1996|title=The French Revolution, 1770\u20131814: 1770\u20131814|publisher=Blackwell Publishing|location=France|isbn=978-0-631-20299-8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1qN-KifyMncC&pg=PA124&lpg=PA124}}\n* {{cite book|last=Garrioch|first=David|title=La fabrique du Paris r\u00e9volutionnaire|year=2015|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte/Poche|isbn=978-2-707