icon|SPA}} [[Xavi Vierge]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/09/05/vierge-to-join-petronas-sprinta-racing-for-2020/307194|title=Vierge to join Petronas Sprinta Racing for 2020|accessdate= 4 September 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|FIN}} [[Ajo Motorsport|Red Bull KTM Ajo ]]\n| align=\"center\" | 45\n| {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Tetsuta Nagashima]]\n| 1\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 88\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Jorge Mart\u00edn (motorcyclist)|Jorge Mart\u00edn]]\n| 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sky Racing Team by VR46|SKY Racing Team VR46]]\n|align=center| 10\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Luca Marini]]\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 72\n|{{Flagicon|ITA}} [[Marco Bezzecchi]]\n| 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{flagicon|CHE}} [[Forward Racing|MV Agusta Temporary Forward]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[MV Agusta]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |F2\n|align=center| 24\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Simone Corsi]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/933601/1/moto2-corsi-replace-aegerter-mv|title=Corsi to replace Aegerter at MV|date=11 November 2019|website=Crash|language=en|access-date=13 November 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 62\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Stefano Manzi]]<ref name=\":1\" />\n| 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{flagicon|NLD}} [[RW Racing GP|NTS RW Racing GP]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[NTS Co., Ltd.|NTS]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |NH7\n| align=\"center\" | 2\n| {{flagicon|SWI}} [[Jesko Raffin]]\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 64\n| {{flagicon|NED}} [[Bo Bendsneyder]]\n| 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Aspar Team]]\n!rowspan=4| [[Speed Up]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | SF20T\n|align=center| 44\n|{{Flagicon|Spain}} [[Ar\u00f3n Canet]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/08/20/aron-canet-signs-with-angel-nieto-squad-for-2020-moto2/305293|title=Aron Canet signs with Angel Nieto squad for 2020 Moto2\u2122|accessdate= 20 August 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 55\n| {{flagicon|MYS}} [[Hafizh Syahrin]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/930558/1/hafizh-syahrin-secures-moto2-return|title=Thailand: Hafizh Syahrin secures Moto2 return|work=crash.net|publisher=[[Peter McLaren]]}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Speed Up|Speed Up Racing]]\n|align=center| 9\n| {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Jorge Navarro]]\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 21\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Fabio Di Giannantonio]]\n| 1\n|-\n| colspan=6 align=center| Source:<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/09/03/how-is-the-2020-moto2-grid-currently-looking/307113|title=How is the 2020 Moto2\u2122 grid currently looking?|date= 3 September 2019|accessdate= 22 September 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n|}\n|valign=\"top\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2|Key\n|-\n| Regular rider\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n| Wildcard rider\n|- style=\"background:#ffcccc;\"\n| {{nowrap|Replacement rider}}\n|}\n|}\n\n* All teams use series-specified [[Dunlop Tyres|Dunlop]] tyres and [[Triumph Motorcycles Ltd|Triumph]] 765cc [[Straight-three engine|3-cylinder engines]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2017/06/03/triumph-announced-as-moto2-engine-supplier-from-2019/230116|title=Triumph announced as Moto2\u2122 engine supplier from 2019|last=|first=|date=3 June 2017|website=MotoGP.com|publisher=Dorna Sports|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170624064624/http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2017/06/03/triumph-announced-as-moto2-engine-supplier-from-2019/230116|archive-date=24 June 2017|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref>.\n\n===Team changes===\n* [[KTM]] withdrew from Moto2 to focus on their MotoGP and Moto3 programmes<ref name=\"KTMout\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/moto2/news/tech3-ktm-withdrawal-bezzecchi-oettl/4513325/|title=Tech 3 follows KTM in pulling out of Moto2|first=Valentin|last=Khorounzhiy|date=14 August 2019|website=Motorsport.com|language=en|access-date=25 November 2019}}</ref>, resulting in the following:\n** American Racing KTM and [[Ajo Motorsport]] switched to using [[Kalex]] bikes.\n** [[\u00c1ngel Nieto Team]] switched to [[Speed Up]] machines.\n** [[Tech 3|Tech3]] switched to a Moto3 programme.<ref name=\"KTMout\"></ref>\n* Sport organizer [[Dorna Sports]] moved to prohibit single-entry teams<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/moto2/news/entry-list-2020-30-bikes/4548021/|title=Moto2 grid cut to 30 bikes for 2020 season|first=Jamie|last=Klein|date=26 September 2019|website=Motorsport.com|language=en|access-date=25 November 2019}}</ref>, resulting in the following:\n** Both [[Gresini Racing|Federal Oil Gresini Moto2]] and [[SIC Racing Team|Petronas Sprinta Racing]] expanded to two bikes for the first time since the 2014 season.\n** Kiefer Racing and Tasca Racing Scuderia Moto2 withdrew from Moto2.\n* Angel Nieto Team reverted to their former name of Aspar.<ref name=\"crash.net\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/934734/1/angel-nieto-team-reverts-aspar-team-name-2020|title=Angel Nieto Team reverts to Aspar Team name from 2020|author=Cobb, Haydn|date=29 November 2019|accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Rider changes===\n* [[Sam Lowes]] moved from Gresini Racing to EG 0,0 Marc VDS, replacing [[Xavi Vierge]], who moved to Petronas Sprinta Racing.\n* [[Ar\u00f3n Canet]] made his debut in [[Moto2]], joining \u00c1ngel Nieto Team and partner with [[Hafizh Syahrin]].\n* [[Lorenzo Dalla Porta]] made his debut in Moto2 with Italtrans Racing Team, replacing [[Andrea Locatelli]].\n* [[Jesko Raffin]] returned to Moto2 with NTS RW Racing GP, where he already rode at the first three events and the last four races before Valencia in 2019 as a replacement rider for [[Steven Odendaal]], whom he will also now replace permanently.\n* [[Marco Bezzecchi]] moved to Sky Racing Team VR46, replacing [[Nicol\u00f2 Bulega]], who moved to Federal Oil Gresini Racing.\n* [[Jake Dixon]] moved to Petronas Sprinta Racing, replacing [[Khairul Idham Pawi]], who returned to Moto3.\n* [[Marcos Ram\u00edrez (motorcyclist)|Marcos Ram\u00edrez]] made his debut in Moto2, joining American Racing Team to replace [[Iker Lecuona]].\n* [[Hafizh Syahrin]] returned to [[Moto2]] after two seasons with Tech 3 in MotoGP, joining Gaviota \u00c1ngel Nieto Team.\n* [[Andi Farid Izdihar]] replaced [[Dimas Ekky Pratama]] at IDEMITSU Honda Team Asia.\n* [[Edgar Pons]] returned full-time to Moto2, joining Federal Oil Gresini Racing.\n*[[Simone Corsi]] returned to [[Forward Racing]], replacing [[Dominique Aegerter]] who joined Dynavolt Intact in [[MotoE World Cup]]. Previously Corsi raced for Forward Racing between 2013 and 2015.\n*[[Kasma Daniel Kasmayudin]] made his debut in [[Moto2]], joining ONEXOX TKKR SAG Team from FIM CEV Moto2.\n*[[Augusto Fern\u00e1ndez (motorcyclist)|Augusto Fern\u00e1ndez]] moves from [[Pons Racing]] to fill the empty seat at [[Marc VDS Racing Team|Marc VDS]] after [[Alex M\u00e1rquez]]'s promotion to MotoGP with [[Repsol Honda]]. His seat at Pons Racing was filled by [[H\u00e9ctor Garz\u00f3]].\n\n==Calendar==\nThe following Grands Prix are scheduled to take place in 2020:<ref>{{cite news|title=2020 MotoGP calendar confirmed|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/935546/1/2020-motogp-calendar-confirmed|date=23 January 2020|accessdate=23 January 2020|work=Crash.net|publisher=CMG}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n!Round\n!Date\n![[List of Grand Prix motorcycle races|Grand Prix]]\n![[List of Grand Prix motorcycle circuits|Circuit]]\n|-\n!1\n|8 March\n| {{flagicon|QAT}} [[Qatar motorcycle Grand Prix|QNB Grand Prix of Qatar]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/03/07/motogp-to-race-at-losail-international-circuit-until-2031/285417|title=MotoGP\u2122 to race at Losail International Circuit until 2031|date=7 March 2019|accessdate=7 March 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| [[Losail International 