oming-to-texas-racing-2|title=MotoGP is Coming to Texas|date=13 April 2011|accessdate=13 April 2011|work=Cycleworld|publisher=Cycleworld}}</ref>\n| [[Circuit of the Americas]], [[Austin, Texas|Austin]]\n|-\n!17\n|22 November\n| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Argentine motorcycle Grand Prix|Gran Premio Motul de la Rep\u00fablica Argentina]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2018/12/11/argentina-to-host-motogp-until-2021/281266|title=Argentina to host MotoGP\u2122 until 2021|date=11 December 2018|accessdate=11 December 2018|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| {{nowrap|[[Aut\u00f3dromo Termas de R\u00edo Hondo]], [[Termas de Rio Hondo]]}}\n|-\n!18\n|29 November\n| {{flagicon|Valencia}} [[Valencian Community motorcycle Grand Prix|Gran Premio Motul de la Comunitat Valenciana]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motorsport.com/motogp/news/valencia-extends-motogp-contract-until-2021-828582/828582/|title=Valencia extends MotoGP contract until 2021|date=20 September 2016|accessdate=20 September 2016|work=Motorsport.com|publisher=[[Motorsport.com]]}}</ref>\n| [[Circuit Ricardo Tormo]], [[Valencia]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" |Postponed races:\n|-\n!&ndash;\n|<s>3 May</s>\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Spanish motorcycle Grand Prix|Gran Premio Red Bull de Espa\u00f1a]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/motor/motogp/20180801/451186163306/jerez-tres-anos-mas-en-el-mundial-de-motogp.html|title=Jerez, tres a\u00f1os m\u00e1s en el Mundial de MotoGP|date=1 August 2018|work=Mundo Deportivo|accessdate=1 August 2018|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo]]}}</ref>\n|[[Circuito de Jerez-\u00c1ngel Nieto]], [[Jerez de la Frontera]]\n|-\n!&ndash;\n|<s>17 May</s>\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[French motorcycle Grand Prix|SHARK Helmets Grand Prix de France]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2018/05/19/french-gp-held-at-le-mans-until-2026/259085|title=French GP held at Le Mans until 2026|date=19 May 2018|accessdate=19 May 2018|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| [[Circuit Bugatti]], [[Le Mans]]\n|}\n\n===Calendar changes===\n* The Argentine and Americas Grands Prix swapped places in the calendar order.\n* The German and Dutch Grand Prix also swapped places, with Germany moving to 21 June, while the Netherlands remains in its traditional position on the final weekend of June.\n* The Finnish Grand Prix was reintroduced to the calendar after a 38-year absence. The venue hosting the round will be the new [[Kymi Ring]], instead of the [[Tampere Circuit]] used in 1962 and 1963 or the [[Imatra Circuit]] which hosted the round until 1982.\n* The Aragon Grand Prix was moved from the last week of September to the first week of October. It was later returned to its original schedule to allow for the rescheduled Thailand Grand Prix.\n\n===Calendar changes as a reaction to coronavirus pandemic===\nThe season calendar has been significantly affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], leading to the cancellation or postponement of many races.\n\n*The Thailand Grand Prix was moved from being the 15th round of 2019 to the 2nd round of 2020. However, the race was later moved due to [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|COVID-19]] concerns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/sports/1869749/buriram-motogp-postponed-indefinitely-due-to-coronavirus|title=Buriram MotoGP postponed indefinitely due to coronavirus|publisher=Bangkok Post Public Company Limited |website=www.bangkokpost.com|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> It was later confirmed to take place on 4 October, shifting the Aragon Grand Prix forward by a week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2020/03/05/updated-2020-motogp-calendar-officially-confirmed/322424|title=UPDATED: 2020 MotoGP\u2122 calendar officially confirmed|last=|first=|date=5 March 2020|website=MotoGP.com|publisher=Dorna Sports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n*The [[Motorcycle Grand Prix of the Americas|Grand Prix of the Americas]] was postponed from 5 April to 15 November after the [[Austin, Texas|City of Austin]] implemented a state of emergency. The [[Valencian Community motorcycle Grand Prix|Valencian Grand Prix]] was subsequently shifted back by one week to  22 November to accommodate the Austin rescheduling.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2020/03/10/red-bull-grand-prix-of-the-americas-rescheduled-for-november/327852|title=Red Bull Grand Prix of the Americas rescheduled for November|last=|first=|date=10 March 2020|website=|publisher=Dorna Sports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n*The [[Argentine motorcycle Grand Prix|Argentine Grand Prix]] was postponed to 22 November, further shifting the finale in Valencia to 29 November.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2020/03/11/motul-argentina-grand-prix-rescheduled-for-november/327976|title=Motul Argentina Grand Prix rescheduled for November|last=|first=|date=11 March 2020|website=MotoGP.com|publisher=Dorna Sports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n*The [[Spanish motorcycle Grand Prix|Spanish Grand Prix]] was postponed on 26 March with a replacement date to be determined.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2020/03/26/red-bull-gran-premio-de-espana-postponed/328557|title=Red Bull Gran Premio de Espa\u00f1a postponed|last=|first=|date=26 March 2020|website=MotoGP.com|publisher=Dorna Sports|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n*The [[French motorcycle Grand Prix|French Grand Prix]] was postponed on 2 April with a replacement date to be determined.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2020/04/02/shark-helmets-grand-prix-de-france-postponed/328743|title=SHARK Helmets Grand Prix de France postponed|last=|first=|date=2 April 2020|website=MotoGP.com|publisher=Dorna Sports|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n