 |issn=0139-0600 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Rubinstein |first=Nicolai |editor1-last=Burns |editor1-first=J. H. |editor2-last=Goldie |editor2-first=Mark |title=The Cambridge History of Political Thought, 1450\u20131700 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1991 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/cambridgehistory0000unse_h8y6/page/30 30\u201365] |chapter=Italian political thought, 1450\u20131530 |isbn=0-521-24716-0 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/cambridgehistory0000unse_h8y6/page/30 }}\n*{{cite book |last=\u0160mahel |first=Franti\u0161ek |authorlink=Franti\u0161ek \u0160mahel |editor1-last=P\u00e1nek |editor1-first=Jaroslav |editor2-last=T\u016fma |editor2-first=Old\u0159ich | title=A History of the Czech Lands |publisher=Charles University in Prague |year=2011 |pages=149\u2013169 |chapter=The Hussite Revolution (1419\u20131471) |isbn=978-80-246-1645-2|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Tanner |first=Marcus |year=2009 |title=The Raven King: Matthias Corvinus and the Fate of his Lost Library |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=978-0-300-15828-1 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Teke |first=Zsuzsa |editor-last=Solymosi |editor-first=L\u00e1szl\u00f3 | title=Magyarorsz\u00e1g t\u00f6rt\u00e9neti kronol\u00f3gi\u00e1ja, I: a kezdetekt\u0151l 1526-ig ''[Historical Chronology of Hungary, Volume I: From the Beginning to 1526]'' |publisher=Akad\u00e9miai Kiad\u00f3 |year=1981 |pages=79\u2013187 |chapter=A k\u00f6z\u00e9pkori magyar \u00e1llam vir\u00e1gz\u00e1sa \u00e9s buk\u00e1sa, 1301\u20131526: 1458\u20131490 [Flourishing and Fall of Medieval Hungary, 1301\u20131526: 1458\u20131490] |isbn=963-05-2661-1|ref=harv|language=hu}}\n*{{cite book |last=Verspohl |first=Franz-Joachim |year=2007 |title=Michelangelo Buonarroti und Leonardo Da Vinci: Republikanischer Alltag und K\u00fcnstlerkonkurrenz in Florenz zwischen 1501 und 1505 |publisher=Wallstein Verlag |language=de |isbn=978-3-8353-0216-7|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Waldman |first=Louis Alexander |last2=Farbaky |first2=P\u00e9ter |year=2011 |title=Italy & Hungary: Humanism and Art in the Early Renaissance |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l-OKuQAACAAJ |publisher=Harvard University Graduate School of Design |isbn=0-674-06346-5|ref=harv}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Refbegin}}\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=B\u00e1r\u00e1ny |editor1-first=Attila |editor2-last=Gy\u00f6rk\u00f6s |editor2-first=Attila | title=Matthias and his Legacy: Cultural and Political Encounters between East and West |publisher=University of Debrecen |year=2008 |isbn=978-963-473-276-1}}\n*{{cite book |last=Birnbaum |first=Marianna D. |year=1996 |title=The Orb and the Pen: Janus Pannonius, Matthias Corvinus and the Buda Court |publisher=Balassi Kiad\u00f3 |isbn=963-506-087-4}}\n*{{cite book |editor1-last=Farbaky |editor1-first=P\u00e9ter |editor2-last=Spekner |editor2-first=Enik\u0151 |editor3-last=Szende |editor3-first=Katalin |display-editors = 3 |editor4-last=V\u00e9gh |editor4-first=Andr\u00e1s | title=Matthias Corvinus, the King: Tradition and Renewal in the Hungarian Royal Court 1458\u20131490 |publisher=Budapest History Museum |year=2008 |isbn=978-963-9340-69-5}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Farbaky |first1=Peter |last2=Waldman |first2=Louis A. |title=Italy & Hungary: Humanism and Art in the Early Renaissance |year=2011 |publisher=Harvard University Press |isbn=9780674063464}}\n*{{cite book |last=Feuer-T\u00f3th |first=R\u00f3zsa |year=1990 |title=Art and Humanism in Hungary in the Age of Matthias Corvinus |publisher=Akad\u00e9miai Kiad\u00f3 |isbn=963-05-5646-4}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Gastgeber |first1=Christian |last2=Mitsiou |first2=Ekaterini |last3=Pop |first3=Ioan-Aurel |last4=Popovi\u0107 |first4=Mihailo |last5=Preiser-Kapeller |first5=Johannes |last6=Simon |first6=Alexandru |year=2011 |title=Matthias Corvinus und seine Zeit: Europa am \u00dcbergang vom Mittelalter zur Neuzeit zwischen Wien und Konstantinopel ''[Matthias Corvinus and His Time: Europe in Transition from the Middle Ages to Modern Times between Vienna and Constantinople]''|publisher= David Brown Book Company |isbn=978-3-7001-6891-1|language=de}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Klaniczay |first1=Tibor |last2=Jankovics |first2=J\u00f3zsef |year=1994 |title=Matthias Corvinus and the Humanism in Central Europe |publisher=Balassi Kiad\u00f3 |isbn=963-7873-72-4}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Hungary}}\n{{Commons}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20170809035828/http://showme.physics.drexel.edu/thury/Matyas.html ''The Squash and the Colt''], a folk tale reflecting Matthias' wisdom and sense of justice\n*[http://www.corvina.oszk.hu ''Bibliotheca Corviniana Digitalis''&nbsp;\u2013 National Sz\u00e9ch\u00e9nyi Library, Hungary]\n*[http://www.euratlas.com/big/big1500.htm Map of Europe in 1500.]\n*{{Cite CE1913|wstitle=Matthias Corvinus |short=x}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou| [[Hunyadi family|House of Hunyadi]] | 23 February | 1443 | 6 April | 1490 }}\n{{S-reg}}\n|-\n{{S-vac| last=[[Ladislaus the Posthumous|Ladislaus V]]}}\n{{S-ttl| rows=1 | title=[[King of Hungary]] and [[King of Croatia|Croatia]]| years=1458\u20131490}}\n{{S-aft| rows=2 | after=[[Ladislaus II of Bohemia and Hungary|Vladislaus II]]}}\n{{S-bef| rows=1 | before=[[George of Pod\u011bbrady|George]]}}\n{{S-dis| rows=1 | title=[[King of Bohemia]]| years=1469\u20131490|by=[[George of Pod\u011bbrady|George]] and [[Ladislaus II of Bohemia and Hungary|Vladislaus II]]}}\n{{S-bef| rows=1 | before=[[Frederick III, Holy Roman Emperor|Frederick V]]}}\n{{S-dis| rows=1 | title=[[Duke of Austria]]| years=1487\u20131490|by=[[Frederick III, Holy Roman Emperor|Frederick V]]}}\n{{S-aft| rows=1 | after=[[Frederick III, Holy Roman Emperor|Frederick V]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Hungarian kings}}\n{{Monarchs of Bohemia}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Matthias Corvinus Of Hungary}}\n[[Category:1443 births]]\n[[Category:1490 deaths]]\n[[Category:15th-century rulers of Austria]]\n[[Category:People from Cluj-Napoca]]\n[[Category:Kings of Hungary]]\n[[Category:Kings of Croatia]]\n[[Category:Medieval child rulers]]\n[[Category:Hungarian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Hunyadi family]]\n[[Category:History of Cluj-Napoca]]\n[[Category:Pretenders to the Bohemian throne]]\n[[Category:15th-century Hungarian nobility]]\n[[Category:15th-century monarchs in Europe]]\n[[Category:Burials at Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r Cathedral]]\n[[Category:Hungarian book and manuscript collectors]]\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matthias_Corvinus"}
{"title_page": "Denan Kemp", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Dean Kemp}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name           = Denan Kemp\n|fullname       = Denan Kemp\n|image          = Denan Kemp (Brisbane Broncos vs. Canberra Raiders 2008).jpg\n|imagesize      = 150px\n|caption        = \n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1987|05|11|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]]\n|height         = {{convert|181|cm|ftin|abbr=on}}\n|weight         = {{convert|87|kg|stlb|abbr=on}}\n|position       = {{rlp|WG|FB|CE}}\n|club1          = [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|year1start     = 2007\n|year1end       = 08\n|appearances1   = 28\n|tries1         = 20\n|goals1         = 0\n|fieldgoals1    = 0\n|points1        = 80\n|club2          = {{nowrap|[[New Zealand Warriors]]}}\n|year2start     = 2009\n|year2end       = \n|appearances2   = 10\n|tries2         = 1\n|goals2         = 21\n|fieldgoals2    = 0\n|points2        = 46\n|club3          = [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|year3start     = 2010\n|year3end       = \n|appearances3   = 4\n|tries3         = 1\n|goals3         = 0\n|fieldgoals3    = 0\n|points3        = 4\n|updated        = 1 February 2019\n|source         = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/denan-kemp/summary.html|title=Denan Kemp - Career Stats & Summary - Rugby League Project|website=Rugbyleagueproject.org}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Denan Kemp''' is an Australian former professional [[rugby league]] footballer who played in the 2000s and 2010s and is best known for his stints in the [[National Rugby League]] (NRL). Kemp's position of choice was on the {{rlp|wg}}. He played in the NRL for the [[Brisbane Broncos]], the [[New Zealand Warriors]] and the [[St George Illawarra Dragons]]. He also had a brief stint in [[rugby union]] in 2011, playing for [[Southern Districts Rugby Club|Southern Districts]] in the [[Shute Shield]] competition.\n\n==Early years==\nKemp has a big nose and attended St Michaels College. Kemp went on to play rugby league with the [[Wests Panthers|Brisbane Wests]] in the [[Queensland Cup]] before joining Brisbane Broncos feeder club, the [[Toowoomba Clydesdales]]. He then was transferred to the [[Aspley Broncos]] in 2007 by the Brisbane Broncos.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.smh.com.au/rugby-league/league-news/with-aussie-accent-horo-says-hes-a-kiwi-at-heart-20100828-13wtn.html| work=The Sydney Morning Herald| date=29 August 2010| title=With Aussie accent, Horo says he's a Kiwi at heart}}</ref><ref>http://everythingturkish.com.au/turkish-sports/rugby-and-turks/</ref>\n\n==Brisbane==\nKemp made his [[National Rugby League|first grade]] debut for the Broncos in round 10 of the [[2007 NRL season]], against the [[Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles]]. During the game Kemp scored an individual 75 metre try. This try was voted as the third best of the [[2007 NRL season]] by NRL.com.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/nrl/ugly-manly-sitting-pretty-20070522-gdq726.html/|title=Ugly Manly sitting pretty|website=Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Kemp started the season strongly coming up with four tries in his first three games. He went on to play 24 games for the club in 2008. In round 12 he scored 4 tries while playing against the [[Parramatta Eels]], equaling a club record set by [[Lote Tuqiri]] and [[Steve Renouf]].{{citation needed|date=July 2016}} The record came just hours after he had announced that he was joining the [[New Zealand Warriors]] for the 2009 season. When not selected for the first grade side, Kemp turned out for the [[Norths Devils]] in the [[Queensland Cup]].<ref>[http://www.globalrugbyleague.com/news/130/ARTICLE/1675/2008-03-14.html QLD Cup preview] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514034601/http://www.globalrugbyleague.com/news/130/ARTICLE/1675/2008-03-14.html |date=14 May 2008}} ''globalrugbyleague.com'', 14 March 2008</ref>\n\nKemp was Brisbane's top try-scorer in 2008 and was named the club's rookie of the year.<ref>[http://www.rleague.com/db/player/k/kemp_denan/index.php Thaiday wins Paul Morgan Medal] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090311071353/http://www.rleague.com/db/player/k/kemp_denan/index.php |date=11 March 2009}} ''rleague.com'', 16 October 2008</ref>\n\n==New Zealand Warriors==\nOn 28 May 2008, the [[New Zealand Warriors]] announced that they had signed Kemp for the 2009 and 2010 seasons.<ref>[http://warriors.sitesuite.ws/plugins/newsfeed.cgi?rm=content&plugin_data_id=23613 Vodafone Warriors Sign Brisbane Speedster Kemp For Two Years] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720190443/http://warriors.sitesuite.ws/plugins/newsfeed.cgi?rm=content&plugin_data_id=23613|date=20 July 2008}} ''warriors.co.nz''</ref><ref name=\"TVNZ_1805501\">{{cite web|url=http://tvnz.co.nz/view/page/1318360/1805501|title=Warriors sign flying Kemp|date=29 May 2008|work=[[Television New Zealand]]|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> Whilst at the Warriors he took on goal-kicking responsibilities for the club for the first half of the 2009 season.\n\nIn round 2 of the 2009 season, Kemp kicked the match winning conversion from the sideline to defeat the [[Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles]] with 28 seconds left. However, for much of the season Kemp could not break into the first grade side, instead he was assigned to [[Otahuhu Leopards|Otahuhu]] and played for the [[Auckland Vulcans]] in the [[NSW Cup]]. Near the end of the season he asked for a release so he could return to Queensland to rebuild his National Rugby League career.<ref>[http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56402/Default.aspx Warriors release winger Kemp] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827222744/http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56402/Default.aspx |date=27 August 2009 }} ''nrl.com'', 24 August 2009</ref><ref name=\"NZ_Herald_10592904\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=10592904&ref=rss|title=Warriors: Kemp given release|date=24 August 2009|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> Kemp played in ten games for the Warriors, scoring 46 points.\n\n==Second stint with Brisbane==\nOn 16 September 2009, Kemp announced that he re-signed with the [[Brisbane Broncos]] for the [[2010 NRL season]], after being granted an early release from the final year of his contract with the Warriors.<ref>[http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56748/Default.aspx Kemp coming home to Broncos] ''nrl.com'', 16 September 2009</ref> however, injury prevented him from claiming a full-time spot in the first grade side. In round 1 2010, against the [[North Queensland Cowboys]], he scored the final try which won the game for the Broncos 30-24. He played for the [[Wynnum Manly Seagulls]] in the 2011 [[Queensland Cup]], before joining the [[Australian Rugby Union]] in April 2011.<ref>[http://www.rleague.com/content/article.php?id=38729 Round 1 Queensland Intrust Super Cup Preview] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110403050854/http://www.rleague.com/content/article.php?id=38729|date=3 April 2011}} ''rleague.com'', 18 March 2011</ref><ref name=\"dragons\"/>\n\n==Rugby union==\nIn April 2011 Kemp signed a contract with the [[Australian Rugby Union]] and was a part of the [[Australia national rugby sevens team|Australian Sevens squad]] that traveled to London for the [[2011 London Sevens|IRB Sevens]].\n\nKemp turned out during the 2011 season for the [[Southern Districts Rugby Club]] side in Sydney's [[Shute Shield]].<ref name=\"dragons\"/>\n\n==St George Illawarra==\nOn 20 November 2011, Kemp signed for one year with the [[St George Illawarra Dragons]] in 2012.<ref name=\"dragons\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dragons.com.au/?s=article-display&id=45201|title=Kemp Joins Dragons for 2012|date=20 November 2011|work=www.dragons.com.au|accessdate=20 November 2011|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63KJUNsft?url=http://www.dragons.com.au/?s=article-display&id=45201|archivedate=20 November 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nKemp played in the [[Charity Shield (NRL)|2012 Charity Shield]] game for the Dragons, but never took the field in a first-grade game, as he was mainly relegated to the club's [[NSW Cup]] side, the [[Illawarra Cutters]].\n\n==Third stint with Brisbane==\nOn 18 January 2013, Kemp signed a one-year deal to return to the Broncos in hopes of another revival of his career. However, he failed to play a single game for the Broncos throughout the entire [[2013 NRL season]], and was released at the season's end. Following his release, Kemp decided to retire from rugby league.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://commentaryboxsports.com/australian/nrl/cbs-sounding-the-siren-no-1-denan-kemp.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=30 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201030924/http://commentaryboxsports.com/australian/nrl/cbs-sounding-the-siren-no-1-denan-kemp.html |archive-date=1 December 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kemp, Denan}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Australian rugby league players]]\n[[Category:Australian rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Australian international rugby sevens players]]\n[[Category:Male rugby sevens players]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Broncos players]]\n[[Category:New Zealand Warriors players]]\n[[Category:Redcliffe Dolphins players]]\n[[Category:Wynnum Manly Seagulls players]]\n[[Category:Illawarra Cutters players]]\n[[Category:Toowoomba Clydesdales players]]\n[[Category:Wests Panthers players]]\n[[Category:Norths Devils players]]\n[[Category:Otahuhu Leopards players]]\n[[Category:Auckland rugby league team players]]\n[[Category:Rugby league wingers]]\n[[Category:Rugby league fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Gold Coast, Queensland]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian people of New Zealand descent]]\n[[Category:Rugby league players from Queensland]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Dean Kemp}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox rugby league biography\n|name           = Denan Kemp\n|fullname       = Denan Kemp\n|image          = Denan Kemp (Brisbane Broncos vs. Canberra Raiders 2008).jpg\n|imagesize      = 150px\n|caption        = \n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1987|05|11|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]]\n|height         = {{convert|181|cm|ftin|abbr=on}}\n|weight         = {{convert|87|kg|stlb|abbr=on}}\n|position       = {{rlp|WG|FB|CE}}\n|club1          = [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|year1start     = 2007\n|year1end       = 08\n|appearances1   = 28\n|tries1         = 20\n|goals1         = 0\n|fieldgoals1    = 0\n|points1        = 80\n|club2          = {{nowrap|[[New Zealand Warriors]]}}\n|year2start     = 2009\n|year2end       = \n|appearances2   = 10\n|tries2         = 1\n|goals2         = 21\n|fieldgoals2    = 0\n|points2        = 46\n|club3          = [[Brisbane Broncos]]\n|year3start     = 2010\n|year3end       = \n|appearances3   = 4\n|tries3         = 1\n|goals3         = 0\n|fieldgoals3    = 0\n|points3        = 4\n|updated        = 1 February 2019\n|source         = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/players/denan-kemp/summary.html|title=Denan Kemp - Career Stats & Summary - Rugby League Project|website=Rugbyleagueproject.org}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Denan Kemp''' is an Australian former professional [[rugby league]] footballer who played in the 2000s and 2010s and is best known for his stints in the [[National Rugby League]] (NRL). Kemp's position of choice was on the {{rlp|wg}}. He played in the NRL for the [[Brisbane Broncos]], the [[New Zealand Warriors]] and the [[St George Illawarra Dragons]]. He also had a brief stint in [[rugby union]] in 2011, playing for [[Southern Districts Rugby Club|Southern Districts]] in the [[Shute Shield]] competition.\n\n==Early years==\nKemp attended St Michaels College. Kemp went on to play rugby league with the [[Wests Panthers|Brisbane Wests]] in the [[Queensland Cup]] before joining Brisbane Broncos feeder club, the [[Toowoomba Clydesdales]]. He then was transferred to the [[Aspley Broncos]] in 2007 by the Brisbane Broncos.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.smh.com.au/rugby-league/league-news/with-aussie-accent-horo-says-hes-a-kiwi-at-heart-20100828-13wtn.html| work=The Sydney Morning Herald| date=29 August 2010| title=With Aussie accent, Horo says he's a Kiwi at heart}}</ref><ref>http://everythingturkish.com.au/turkish-sports/rugby-and-turks/</ref>\n\n==Brisbane==\nKemp made his [[National Rugby League|first grade]] debut for the Broncos in round 10 of the [[2007 NRL season]], against the [[Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles]]. During the game Kemp scored an individual 75 metre try. This try was voted as the third best of the [[2007 NRL season]] by NRL.com.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/nrl/ugly-manly-sitting-pretty-20070522-gdq726.html/|title=Ugly Manly sitting pretty|website=Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Kemp started the season strongly coming up with four tries in his first three games. He went on to play 24 games for the club in 2008. In round 12 he scored 4 tries while playing against the [[Parramatta Eels]], equaling a club record set by [[Lote Tuqiri]] and [[Steve Renouf]].{{citation needed|date=July 2016}} The record came just hours after he had announced that he was joining the [[New Zealand Warriors]] for the 2009 season. When not selected for the first grade side, Kemp turned out for the [[Norths Devils]] in the [[Queensland Cup]].<ref>[http://www.globalrugbyleague.com/news/130/ARTICLE/1675/2008-03-14.html QLD Cup preview] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514034601/http://www.globalrugbyleague.com/news/130/ARTICLE/1675/2008-03-14.html |date=14 May 2008}} ''globalrugbyleague.com'', 14 March 2008</ref>\n\nKemp was Brisbane's top try-scorer in 2008 and was named the club's rookie of the year.<ref>[http://www.rleague.com/db/player/k/kemp_denan/index.php Thaiday wins Paul Morgan Medal] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090311071353/http://www.rleague.com/db/player/k/kemp_denan/index.php |date=11 March 2009}} ''rleague.com'', 16 October 2008</ref>\n\n==New Zealand Warriors==\nOn 28 May 2008, the [[New Zealand Warriors]] announced that they had signed Kemp for the 2009 and 2010 seasons.<ref>[http://warriors.sitesuite.ws/plugins/newsfeed.cgi?rm=content&plugin_data_id=23613 Vodafone Warriors Sign Brisbane Speedster Kemp For Two Years] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720190443/http://warriors.sitesuite.ws/plugins/newsfeed.cgi?rm=content&plugin_data_id=23613|date=20 July 2008}} ''warriors.co.nz''</ref><ref name=\"TVNZ_1805501\">{{cite web|url=http://tvnz.co.nz/view/page/1318360/1805501|title=Warriors sign flying Kemp|date=29 May 2008|work=[[Television New Zealand]]|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> Whilst at the Warriors he took on goal-kicking responsibilities for the club for the first half of the 2009 season.\n\nIn round 2 of the 2009 season, Kemp kicked the match winning conversion from the sideline to defeat the [[Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles]] with 28 seconds left. However, for much of the season Kemp could not break into the first grade side, instead he was assigned to [[Otahuhu Leopards|Otahuhu]] and played for the [[Auckland Vulcans]] in the [[NSW Cup]]. Near the end of the season he asked for a release so he could return to Queensland to rebuild his National Rugby League career.<ref>[http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56402/Default.aspx Warriors release winger Kemp] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827222744/http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56402/Default.aspx |date=27 August 2009 }} ''nrl.com'', 24 August 2009</ref><ref name=\"NZ_Herald_10592904\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=10592904&ref=rss|title=Warriors: Kemp given release|date=24 August 2009|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> Kemp played in ten games for the Warriors, scoring 46 points.\n\n==Second stint with Brisbane==\nOn 16 September 2009, Kemp announced that he re-signed with the [[Brisbane Broncos]] for the [[2010 NRL season]], after being granted an early release from the final year of his contract with the Warriors.<ref>[http://www.nrl.com/NewsViews/LatestNews/NewsArticle/tabid/10874/newsId/56748/Default.aspx Kemp coming home to Broncos] ''nrl.com'', 16 September 2009</ref> however, injury prevented him from claiming a full-time spot in the first grade side. In round 1 2010, against the [[North Queensland Cowboys]], he scored the final try which won the game for the Broncos 30-24. He played for the [[Wynnum Manly Seagulls]] in the 2011 [[Queensland Cup]], before joining the [[Australian Rugby Union]] in April 2011.<ref>[http://www.rleague.com/content/article.php?id=38729 Round 1 Queensland Intrust Super Cup Preview] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110403050854/http://www.rleague.com/content/article.php?id=38729|date=3 April 2011}} ''rleague.com'', 18 March 2011</ref><ref name=\"dragons\"/>\n\n==Rugby union==\nIn April 2011 Kemp signed a contract with the [[Australian Rugby Union]] and was a part of the [[Australia national rugby sevens team|Australian Sevens squad]] that traveled to London for the [[2011 London Sevens|IRB Sevens]].\n\nKemp turned out during the 2011 season for the [[Southern Districts Rugby Club]] side in Sydney's [[Shute Shield]].<ref name=\"dragons\"/>\n\n==St George Illawarra==\nOn 20 November 2011, Kemp signed for one year with the [[St George Illawarra Dragons]] in 2012.<ref name=\"dragons\">{{cite news|url=http://www.dragons.com.au/?s=article-display&id=45201|title=Kemp Joins Dragons for 2012|date=20 November 2011|work=www.dragons.com.au|accessdate=20 November 2011|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63KJUNsft?url=http://www.dragons.com.au/?s=article-display&id=45201|archivedate=20 November 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nKemp played in the [[Charity Shield (NRL)|2012 Charity Shield]] game for the Dragons, but never took the field in a first-grade game, as he was mainly relegated to the club's [[NSW Cup]] side, the [[Illawarra Cutters]].\n\n==Third stint with Brisbane==\nOn 18 January 2013, Kemp signed a one-year deal to return to the Broncos in hopes of another revival of his career. However, he failed to play a single game for the Broncos throughout the entire [[2013 NRL season]], and was released at the season's end. Following his release, Kemp decided to retire from rugby league.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://commentaryboxsports.com/australian/nrl/cbs-sounding-the-siren-no-1-denan-kemp.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=30 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201030924/http://commentaryboxsports.com/australian/nrl/cbs-sounding-the-siren-no-1-denan-kemp.html |archive-date=1 December 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kemp, Denan}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Australian rugby league players]]\n[[Category:Australian rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Australian international rugby sevens players]]\n[[Category:Male rugby sevens players]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Broncos players]]\n[[Category:New Zealand Warriors players]]\n[[Category:Redcliffe Dolphins players]]\n[[Category:Wynnum Manly Seagulls players]]\n[[Category:Illawarra Cutters players]]\n[[Category:Toowoomba Clydesdales players]]\n[[Category:Wests Panthers players]]\n[[Category:Norths Devils players]]\n[[Category:Otahuhu Leopards players]]\n[[Category:Auckland rugby league team players]]\n[[Category:Rugby league wingers]]\n[[Category:Rugby league fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Gold Coast, Queensland]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian people of New Zealand descent]]\n[[Category:Rugby league players from Queensland]]\n", "name_user": "1.42.172.135", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEarly years)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denan_Kemp"}
